events.text: Welcome to your new league!
The Jazz traded Felton Spencer and a 1999 1st round pick (UTA) to the Cavaliers for Dan Majerle, Antonio Lang, and Donny Marshall.

The Cavaliers traded Terrell Brandon Sr., Chris Mills, Bobby Phills, John Amaechi, and Michael Cage to the SuperSonics for David Wingate, Vincent Askew, Steve Scheffler, Frank Brickowski Sr., a 1996 1st round pick (SEA), a 1996 2nd round pick (SEA), a 1997 1st round pick (SEA), a 1997 2nd round pick (SEA), and a 1998 1st round pick (SEA).
The Trailblazers traded Buck Williams, Chris Dudley, and a 1999 2nd round pick (POR) to the Cavaliers for Danny Ferry, Tyrone Hill, and Bob Sura.
The Bulls traded Randy Brown, Jud Buechler, Jason Caffey, James Edwards, Jack Haley, a 1996 2nd round pick (CHI), and a 1998 2nd round pick (CHI) to the Trailblazers for Rod Strickland.

The SuperSonics traded John Amaechi, Michael Cage, Sam Perkins, Eric Snow, Ervin Johnson, and a 1999 2nd round pick (SEA) to the Trailblazers for Randy Brown, Jud Buechler, Arvydas Sabonis, and Clifford Robinson.

The Trailblazers traded James Edwards, Sam Perkins, a 1998 2nd round pick (CHI), and a 1999 2nd round pick (SEA) to the Warriors for B.J. Armstrong, Chris Gatling, a 1996 1st round pick (GSW), and a 1996 2nd round pick (GSW).
The Magic traded Brooks Thompson, Jeff Turner, and a 1996 1st round pick (ORL) to the Mavericks for George McCloud and Lucious Harris.
The Spurs traded Doc Rivers, Carl Herrera, Greg Anderson, J.R. Reid, and a 1997 1st round pick (SAS) to the Cavaliers for Chris Dudley and Vincent Askew.

The Trailblazers traded John Amaechi, B.J. Armstrong, Harvey Grant, and Randolph Childress to the Magic for Lucious Harris, Brian Shaw, Anthony Bowie, Jon Koncak, a 1996 2nd round pick (ORL), a 1997 1st round pick (ORL), and a 1997 2nd round pick (ORL).
The Warriors traded Tim Hardaway and a 1998 2nd round pick (CHI) to the Nets for Kenny Anderson.
The Trailblazers traded Eric Snow to the Suns for Chris Carr.
The 76ers traded Jeff Malone, Scott Williams, Elmer Bennett, a 1997 1st round pick (PHI), a 1999 1st round pick (PHI), and a 1999 2nd round pick (PHI) to the Bucks for Vin Baker and Terry Cummings.
The 76ers traded Richard Dumas, Greg Graham, Tim Perry, and a 1998 1st round pick (PHI) to the Warriors for Kenny Anderson and a 1999 2nd round pick (GSW).

The Warriors traded James Edwards, Donyell Marshall, Jerome Kersey, Jon Barry, David Wood, Greg Graham, a 1998 1st round pick (GSW), and a 1999 2nd round pick (SEA) to the Bucks for Glenn Robinson, Shawn Respert, and Lee Mayberry.
The SuperSonics traded Randy Brown, Jud Buechler, Sherell Ford, and a 1998 2nd round pick (SEA) to the Bucks for Jerome Kersey, Johnny Newman, and Randolph Keys.

The Trailblazers traded Jason Caffey, Jack Haley, Michael Cage, Bob Sura, Aaron McKie, Anthony Cook, Dontonio Wingfield, Bill Curley, Reggie Slater, and a 1996 2nd round pick (CHI) to the 76ers for Sharone Wright, Clarence Weatherspoon, and Derrick Alston.

The Jazz traded Dan Majerle, Antonio Lang, Bryon Russell, Antoine Carr, Greg Foster, James Donaldson, Andy Toolson, a 1997 1st round pick (UTA), a 1997 2nd round pick (UTA), a 1998 1st round pick (UTA), and a 1998 2nd round pick (UTA) to the Heat for Alonzo Mourning, LeRon Ellis, and Ronnie Grandison.
The Bucks released Marty Conlon.
The Heat traded Billy Owens to the Pistons for Mark West Sr., Mark Macon, and a 1997 2nd round pick (DET).
